The paper discusses the challenges of developing deep learning models for resource-constrained IoT devices, which falls under the domain of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also focuses on optimizing the quality of service (QoS) of the IoT devices, which can be categorized under embedded systems (cs.EM) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a novel approach for optimizing the deployment configurations of DNN models on FPGAs, which can be categorized under computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) and augmented reality (cs.AR).
